# 10-python — Python rules (auto-attached on *.py)

Mirror of [pr-rules/python.md](mdc:pr-rules/python.md). Read that file in
full for examples.

## Required

- Python **>= 3.8**. No `match`, no `tomllib`, no `str.removeprefix`,
  no PEP 695 generics, no `typing.Self`.
- New / modified modules: `from __future__ import annotations` at the top.
- Entry-point signature: `main(argv=None) -> int`.
- CLI parsing: `argparse.ArgumentParser` only — no click/typer/fire.
- Filesystem: `pathlib.Path`. Always pass `encoding="utf-8"` to `open()`
  and `Path.open()`.
- Imports grouped stdlib → third-party → local with one blank line between
  groups.
- One responsibility per line; no `;`-chained statements.

## Dependencies

- Runtime deps live in `pyproject.toml` `[project.dependencies]`. Do not
  add a runtime dep without flagging it in the PR body.
- Build-system deps live in `[build-system].requires`.
- Allowed runtime set today: `markdownify`, `beautifulsoup4`, `requests`,
  `reportlab`, `pillow`, `pyyaml`, `anthropic` (+ optional `deploy` extra:
  `flask`, `gunicorn`).

## Tests

- pytest only. No `unittest.TestCase` subclasses for new tests.
- New entry point or CLI utility ⇒ at least a smoke test that asserts
  `--help` exits 0 (driven via `subprocess.run`, not direct import).

## Cross-platform

- CI runs on `windows-latest`. Avoid POSIX-only assumptions in tested
  code paths (no Unix signals, no hard-coded `/tmp/`, no shebang-only
  invocations).
